<en-export export-date="20260611T073839Z" application="Evernote" version="11.9.1">
  <note>
    <title>T-A-architectural (scant cells)</title>
    <created>20250428T064618Z</created>
    <updated>20250428T064827Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>ATYPIA OF UNDETERMINED SIGNIFICANCE. </div><div>Sparsely cellular aspirate comprised of follicular cells with architectural atypia. Colloid is absent.</div><div><br/></div><div>TYPE OF SPECIMEN: Thyroid, ___ lobe, fine needle aspiration</div><div>ADEQUACY: Specimen adequacy is limited by scant epithelial cellularity</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: A repeat aspirate may be helpful in order to further characterize the lesion. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>T-A-nuclear</title>
    <created>20250428T064618Z</created>
    <updated>20250506T030637Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>ATYPIA OF UNDETERMINED SIGNIFICANCE. </div><div>Follicular cells, predominantly benign-appearing, with focal nuclear atypia.</div><div><br/></div><div>TYPE OF SPECIMEN: Thyroid, ___ lobe, FNA</div><div>ADEQUACY: Satisfactory for interpretation</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Smears show follicular cells which are predominantly benign appearing, but with occasional nuclear grooves or intranuclear inclusions. Papillary carcinoma cannot be confidently excluded. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>T-A-oncocytic (patient with multiple, bilateral nodules; multinocular goiter)</title>
    <created>20250428T064618Z</created>
    <updated>20250428T065147Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>ATYPIA OF UNDETERMINED SIGNIFICANCE. </div><div>The specimen is moderately cellular and consists almost exclusively of oncocytic cells. Colloid is scant, and there is no apparent increase in lymphoid cells. </div><div>Note: In a patient with multiple nodules, the findings likely represent oncocytic cell hyperplasia in the setting of multinodular goiter; however an oncocytic fol-licular neoplasm cannot be entirely excluded.</div><div><br/></div><div>TYPE OF SPECIMEN: Thyroid, ___ lobe, fine needle aspiration</div><div>ADEQUACY: Satisfactory for interpretation</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>T-B</title>
    <created>20250428T062100Z</created>
    <updated>20250428T062343Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>BENIGN</div><div>Consistent with nodular goiter (follicular nodular disease)</div><div><br/></div><div>TYPE OF SPECIMEN: Thyroid, ___ lobe, fine needle aspiration </div><div>ADEQUACY: Satisfactory for interpretation</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Smears show a macrofollicular lesion composed of moderate to abundant follicular cells arranged in honeycomb flat sheets and some colloid material. Findings are suggestive of nodular goiter.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>T-B-Colloid</title>
    <created>20250428T062219Z</created>
    <updated>20250428T064348Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>BENIGN</div><div>Abundant colloid and rare follicular cells, consistent with follicular nodular disease (colloid nodule)</div><div><br/></div><div>TYPE OF SPECIMEN: Thyroid, ___ lobe, fine needle aspiration</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
